Make sure to apply these changes per revision, in reverse order! Otherwise, you
may corrupt your database. Revert back to the specified revision if necessary.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Changed in revision 35:

Reordered pc monitor services. Nice feature: a default set of services will be
installed whenever a new non-admin pc is added.

./manage dbshell:
mysql> alter table inforecords_monitorservice add column is_default_service
bool not null;
mysql> drop table inforecords_pcmonitorservice;
mysql> alter table inforecords_organization drop column contact_id;
mysql> alter table inforecords_location drop column contact_id;

./manage shell:
In [1]: from inforecords.models import *

In [2]: for pc in Pc.objects.all():
   ...:     pc.install_default_services()
   ...:     
   ...:     


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Changed in revision 34:

Removed country field from the Location model. We already specify a cluster,
so country is not needed.

./manage dbshell:
mysql> alter table inforecords_location drop column country;


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Changed in revision 30.1.2:

Make sure to apply these changes ONLY AFTER you have applied the changes from
revision 31.1. Otherwise, you will lose all stored station passwords.

Dropped upload codes and passwords from the DetectorHisparc model.

./manage dbshell:
mysql> alter table inforecords_detectorhisparc drop column password;
mysql> alter table inforecords_detectorhisparc drop column upload_code;


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Changed in revision 30.1.1:

Passwords are used station-wide, not just for the scintillator device. Added
support for the angle in which skiboxes are placed. Now, we can fully describe
the station layout.

Perform these changes manually:

./manage.py dbshell:
mysql> alter table inforecords_station add column password varchar(40) not null;
mysql> alter table inforecords_detectorhisparc add column scintillator_1_angle double precision null;
mysql> alter table inforecords_detectorhisparc add column scintillator_2_angle double precision null;
mysql> alter table inforecords_detectorhisparc add column scintillator_3_angle double precision null;
mysql> alter table inforecords_detectorhisparc add column scintillator_4_angle double precision null;

./manage.py shell:
In [28]: from inforecords.models import DetectorHisparc, Station

In [29]: for d in DetectorHisparc.objects.select_related().all():
    d.station.password = d.password
    d.station.save()
   ....:     
   ....:     
